---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base title="Cambly vs Lingoda: Which Budget Platform Wins?" description="Compare Cambly vs Lingoda for budget English learners. Pricing, features, teacher quality, and more, honest side-by-side analysis.">
  <Header />
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 pt-6">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-neutral-300 mb-4 flex items-center flex-wrap">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-emerald-400">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      <a href="/compare/" class="hover:text-emerald-400">Comparisons</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      <span class="text-neutral-400">Cambly vs Lingoda</span>
    </nav>
  </div>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">Published April 2026</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Cambly vs Lingoda: Which Budget Platform Wins?</h1>
    <div class="bg-emerald-900/40 border border-emerald-700/50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold mb-2">Quick Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-200">See Guru is our #1 pick for budget learners at $5/hr with 3 free trial lessons. Cambly offers unlimited conversation practice at $9.99/month. Lingoda provides structured group classes from $8/session. The right choice depends on whether you prioritize flexibility or curriculum.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl overflow-x-auto mb-8">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-slate-700">
          <tr>
            <th class="p-4 text-left text-gray-300">Feature</th>
            <th class="p-4 text-center text-white">Cambly</th>
            <th class="p-4 text-center text-white">Lingoda</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-700">
          <tr><td class="p-4 text-gray-300">Starting Price</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-emerald-400 font-semibold">$9.99/month</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-white">$8/session</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-4 text-gray-300">Subscription Type</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-white">Unlimited minutes</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-white">Per-session</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-4 text-gray-300">Lesson Format</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-white">Free conversation</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-white">Structured curriculum</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-4 text-gray-300">Group Classes</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-gray-400">No</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-emerald-400 font-semibold">Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-4 text-gray-300">Native Speakers</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-emerald-400 font-semibold">Yes</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-white">Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-4 text-gray-300">Mobile App</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-emerald-400 font-semibold">Yes</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-white">Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-4 text-gray-300">Certification</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-gray-400">No</td><td class="p-4 text-center text-emerald-400 font-semibold">Yes</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">Cambly Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Cambly positions itself as a conversation practice platform rather than a structured course. For $9.99/month (annual plan), you get unlimited access to native English speakers for 1-on-1 video chats. There is no curriculum, no homework, and no progress tracking. You book a tutor, join a call, and talk.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">The platform connects you with tutors from the US, UK, Australia, and Canada. Sessions range from 15 to 60 minutes and you can join from desktop or mobile. Cambly also offers group sessions called "Cabals" where multiple learners practice together.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Cambly Pros</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Unlimited conversation practice at one flat monthly rate</li>
        <li>Access to native speakers from US, UK, Canada, Australia</li>
        <li>Flexible scheduling with on-demand tutors available 24/7</li>
        <li>Mobile app for learning on the go</li>
        <li>Group "Cabals" sessions included in subscription</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Cambly Cons</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>No structured curriculum or lesson plans</li>
        <li>No way to track progress or set learning goals</li>
        <li>Tutor quality varies significantly between sessions</li>
        <li>Some tutors cancel or reschedule frequently</li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">Lingoda Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Lingoda takes the opposite approach. This Berlin-based platform offers structured group and private English classes taught by qualified, non-native but fluent teachers. Classes follow a curriculum aligned to the CEFR framework, and you earn certificates upon completion.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Sessions cost around $8 per class for group sessions and $15 for private lessons. You can buy class packs or subscribe monthly. Lingoda's teachers are based in Europe, so time zones may not suit learners in Asia or the Americas as well.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Lingoda Pros</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Structured curriculum aligned to CEFR levels (A1-C2)</li>
        <li>Official certification upon completion</li>
        <li>Small group classes (max 6 students) for focused learning</li>
        <li>Private lesson option for personalized attention</li>
        <li>Course materials and homework included</li>
      </ul>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Lingoda Cons</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Higher cost per session compared to Cambly</li>
        <li>Non-native teachers (though fluent and qualified)</li>
        <li>Fixed class schedules require planning ahead</li>
        <li>Time zones may not suit all regions</li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">Head-to-Head: Cambly vs Lingoda</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">The core difference is structure versus flexibility. Cambly is ideal if you want to practice speaking without a plan. Lingoda is better if you want to follow a course and measure progress.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Speaking Practice</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Cambly wins on volume. With unlimited sessions at $9.99/month, you can practice every day without watching costs. Lingoda charges per session, so each conversation has a price tag. If your goal is maximum speaking time at minimum cost, Cambly takes this round.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Curriculum Quality</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Lingoda wins here. Its CEFR-aligned curriculum gives learners a clear path from A1 to C2. Cambly has no curriculum at all. For structured progression and recognized certification, Lingoda is the clear choice.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Teacher Quality</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Both platforms employ qualified teachers. Cambly's tutors are native English speakers from US/UK/AU/CA. Lingoda's teachers are fluent non-native speakers with teaching qualifications. Native accent exposure gives Cambly an edge for pronunciation, but Lingoda's teachers may be more structured in their approach.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Price</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Cambly is significantly cheaper for heavy users. At $9.99/month for unlimited talking, you could have 30+ sessions for the cost of 4 Lingoda classes. However, Lingoda's per-session model lets you learn less intensively without paying for a monthly subscription you will not use.</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">Who Should Choose Cambly</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Learners who want maximum conversation practice on a tight budget</li>
        <li>People who prefer flexible, on-demand scheduling</li>
        <li>Intermediate to advanced speakers wanting to maintain fluency</li>
        <li>Users who prioritize native speaker exposure over curriculum</li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">Who Should Choose Lingoda</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Beginners who need structured lesson plans and clear progression</li>
        <li>Learners seeking official certification for job or study applications</li>
        <li>People who prefer small group classes over 1-on-1 sessions</li>
        <li>Learners comfortable with European time zones</li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">See Guru: A Stronger Alternative</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">See Guru rounds out the budget category with professional tutors at $5/hour starting rate. It offers both 1-on-1 sessions and small groups, with native and fluent teachers available around the clock. For learners who want Cambly's affordability combined with Lingoda's structure, See Guru fills that gap.</p>
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-900/60 to-slate-800 border border-emerald-600/30 rounded-xl p-6 mt-8">
        <h3 class="text-emerald-400 font-bold mb-2">Try See Guru Today</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">See Guru offers professional 1-on-1 English tutoring from $5/hour. No subscription required, book sessions as you need them.</p>
        <a href="/go/see-guru/" rel="sponsored nofollow" class="inline-block bg-emerald-500 hover:bg-emerald-600 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors">View See Guru Plans</a>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-4">FAQ</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Is Cambly cheaper than Lingoda?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Yes. Cambly's unlimited plan costs $9.99/month, while Lingoda charges $8 per session. For heavy learners, Cambly offers better value. For casual learners, Lingoda's per-session model may be more cost-effective.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Does Cambly have a structured curriculum?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">No. Cambly is a conversation practice platform. There are no lesson plans, homework assignments, or progress tracking. You join a call and talk with your tutor. If you need structure, look at Lingoda or See Guru.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Can I earn a certificate with Lingoda?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Yes. Lingoda issues certificates upon completing its curriculum levels. These align with CEFR standards (A1-C2) and may be recognized by employers and educational institutions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Are Lingoda teachers native English speakers?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Lingoda uses qualified non-native English speakers as teachers. They are fluent, trained, and certified. However, if native accent exposure is important to you, Cambly and See Guru offer more access to native speakers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h3 class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">Which platform is better for beginners?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Lingoda is better for beginners who need structured lessons and clear progression. Cambly's free-form conversations can be overwhelming for new learners. See Guru also offers structured beginner courses alongside conversation practice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-8 italic">Disclosure: See Guru links in this article are affiliate links. We may earn a commission if you sign up, at no extra cost to you.</p>
    </div>
  
    <aside class="mt-12 mb-4 p-6 bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Related comparisons</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-base">
        <li><a href="/compare/cambly-vs-see-guru/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300">Cambly vs See Guru</a></li>
        <li><a href="/compare/see-guru-vs-cambly/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300">See Guru vs Cambly</a></li>
        <li><a href="/compare/see-guru-vs-lingoda/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300">See Guru vs Lingoda</a></li>
        <li><a href="/compare/cambly-vs-italki/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300">Cambly vs Italki</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-5 pt-5 border-t border-slate-700 text-sm text-slate-300">
        Want to skip the comparison and just try the option we recommend? <a href="/reviews/see-guru/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">See Guru</a> gives you 3 free lessons with certified teachers, no card required.
      </p>
    </aside>

  </article>
  <Footer />
</Base>
